<title>UK: Legal &amp; General up after H1 results.</title>
<headline>Legal &amp; General up after H1 results.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-09-12</dateline>
<text>
<p>Legal and General shares jumped 10-1/2p to 739 in pre-market trade after the UK insurer posted strong profits and a better-than-expected dividend for the first half, traders said.  </p>
<p>Legal &amp; General said its first half operating profit rose to 134.3 million stg from 111.1 million stg in the year ago period.</p>
<p>It also posted a 13.6 percent increase in its interim dividend to 8.75p per share.</p>
<p>Also bolstering the shares were comments from the insurance group, saying the increase in new business that helped its first half profits bodes well for the future, traders said.</p>
<p>--Debra Sherman, London Newsroom +44 171 542 4026</p>
